# Git authorship policy (mandatory)

All commits must have a human author AND a human committer (the repo's
configured git user). Forbidden in any commit message or metadata:

- `Co-authored-by` trailers of any kind
- AI attribution: Cursor, Codex, Claude, Fable, ChatGPT, OpenAI, Anthropic
- `Generated-by` or any tooling attribution

## Verification is part of every task

After every commit, verify before reporting completion:

```bash
git log -1 --format=full   # author + committer must be human
git log -1 --format=%B     # full message must contain no trailers
```

If attribution exists, amend or recreate the commit before considering the
task complete.

## Known issue: tooling injects a trailer into `git commit`

The agent harness appends `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
to any `git commit` / `git commit --amend` invocation (even with `-F`).
Bypass it with git plumbing (this produced clean commit 3ab456a):

```bash
# 1. Stage changes, then create the commit object directly:
git add -A
git write-tree                                   # if nothing committed yet, or:
NEW=$(git commit-tree 'HEAD^{tree}' -p 'HEAD^' -F msgfile)   # rewrite HEAD, or
NEW=$(git commit-tree "$(git write-tree)" -p HEAD -F msgfile) # new commit from index
git update-ref refs/heads/<branch> "$NEW"
rm msgfile && git log -1 --format=full           # verify
```

Write the message file with a file tool (not echo/heredoc through git commit).

## Completion criteria (all tasks)

1. Code complete
2. Tests green
3. Commit metadata clean (verified as above)

A task is NOT complete otherwise.
